{
  "texts": [
    "Given any integral rectangle R of the form given in (5.17), and i ∈ {0, 1,..., F (R) -1}, we define the cubeQ(R, i) by Q(R, i) = [0, c F (R)] d + p(R) + i c F (R).",
    "(5.18)Note that the cubes Q(R, i) are non-overlapping and form a partition of R.We let R 0 = [0, 1 K] × [0, 1] d. We let Q(R 0, i 0) = Q i for i 0 ∈ {0,..., K -1}.",
    "We let R z 1 i 0 = R(Q i 0, z 1) for z 1 ∈ Ref.",
    "We let Q z 1 i 0,i 1 = Q(R z 1 i 0, i 1)whenever i 0, i 1 ∈ {0,..., K -1} and z 1 ∈ Ref.",
    "We continue inductively."
  ]
}